 {dq}‚Üêevents Event message;event;object;realevent;localize;fn;action;run;Application;handler;‚éïTRAP;GUIroot;suppress;warg;wres;wevent;force;mousing;mouseonce;top;realobject;suppressable
‚çù When any needed Dyalog event is signalled, execute this function directly to perform the appropriate operations.
‚çù Important: This function often operates independently of ‚àÜWI and allows a separate access point into the DeltaWI system when system events call it.
‚çù
‚çù The right argument and result are the standard Dyalog ‚éïDQ event message and action.
‚çù The left argument is a list of APL+Win event names (w/o 'on') that should respond to this Dyalog event, in order.
‚çù The event name 'Event' can be used to invoke Dyalog-style processing, but uses (modified & restricted) Dyalog-style processing syntax.
‚çù This function will also be called explicitly when firing implied events (due to methods or changing properties),
‚çù and will respect 'suppress' if the event name includes an additional '?' (for properties only).
‚çù Note: When firing an implied event, message[2] must be synthesized with an Application reference instead of a (text) event name.
‚çù The terms Internal/Implied/Implicit/Synthetic are used to mean similar things in these descriptive comments.

‚çù Results from ‚àá_onXxxx APL+Win event handlers (and standard Dyalog callback functions) as well as myself:
‚çù       1 = Normal processing continues
‚çù       0 = Normal processing ignored (and abort further processing of pseudo-events and standard APL/Windows handling)
‚çù       A substitute event message for ‚éïDQ to process ‚çù? See if a prototype of this process can work effectively
‚çù       A special explicit returned result, but only when processing an implied event from/for an APL+Win handler

‚çù? What if an event needs to be fired on an object's parent instead? Does the ‚àá_onXxxx routine figure this out for us somehow?

