 ‚çù? And since we often call this implicitly during internal processing, do we want to do the same thing to report back to our internal code (probably OK?)?

 :Hold '‚àÜWI#',‚çï‚éïTID ‚ãÑ top‚Üê1 ‚ãÑ :Else ‚ãÑ top‚Üê0 ‚ãÑ :EndHold                  ‚çù Is this a recursive call? ‚çù? This sequence could be interrupted by an in-thread event that might happen any time (high-priority??)
 :Hold top/'‚àÜWI'('‚àÜWI#',‚çï‚éïTID)                                          ‚çù Make sure we stay single-threaded!

